#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.61"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.61:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.61:0.2"
msgid "6. Avijjāvagga "
msgstr "6. Ignorance "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 61. Paṭhamasabbupādānapariyādānasutta → pariyādinnaṃ 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.61:0.3"
msgid "61. Paṭhamasabbupādānapariyādānasutta "
msgstr "61. The Depletion of All Fuel (1st) "

# NOTE: Upadana has the dual meanings of “grasping “and” fuel”. Normally, grasping predominates. here, however, as shown in SN 12.52, etc, fuel is the dominant metaphor. BB has “exhaustion of all clinging”, which is an incoherent metaphor. See https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/on-grasping-and-fuel/2983
#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.34, sc1
msgctxt "sn35.61:1.1"
msgid "“Sabbupādānapariyādānāya vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I will teach you the principle for depleting all fuel. "

msgctxt "sn35.61:1.2"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha. "
msgstr "Listen … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.61:1.3"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sabbupādānapariyādānāya dhammo? "
msgstr "And what is the principle for depleting all fuel? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.61:1.4"
msgid "Cakkhuñca paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati cakkhuviññāṇaṃ. Tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso. "
msgstr "Eye consciousness arises dependent on the eye and sights. The meeting of the three is contact. "

msgctxt "sn35.61:1.5"
msgid "Phassapaccayā vedanā. "
msgstr "Contact is a condition for feeling. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.61:1.6"
msgid "Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, rūpesupi nibbindati, cakkhuviññāṇepi nibbindati, cakkhusamphassepi nibbindati, vedanāyapi nibbindati. "
msgstr "Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, sights, eye consciousness, eye contact, and feeling. "

#. VAR: pariyādinnaṃ → sabbatthapi evameva dissati
msgctxt "sn35.61:1.7"
msgid "Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimokkhā ‘pariyādinnaṃ me upādānan’ti pajānāti … pe … "
msgstr "Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they are released, they understand: ‘I have completely depleted grasping.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.61:1.8"
msgid "jivhañca paṭicca rase ca uppajjati jivhāviññāṇaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "Ear … nose … tongue … body … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.61:1.9"
msgid "manañca paṭicca dhamme ca uppajjati manoviññāṇaṃ. Tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso. "
msgstr "Mind consciousness arises dependent on the mind and thoughts. The meeting of the three is contact. "

msgctxt "sn35.61:1.10"
msgid "Phassapaccayā vedanā. "
msgstr "Contact is a condition for feeling. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.61:1.11"
msgid "Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako manasmimpi nibbindati, dhammesupi nibbindati, manoviññāṇepi nibbindati manosamphassepi nibbindati, vedanāyapi nibbindati. "
msgstr "Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the mind, thoughts, mind consciousness, mind contact, and feeling. "

msgctxt "sn35.61:1.12"
msgid "Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimokkhā ‘pariyādinnaṃ me upādānan’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they are released, they understand: ‘I have completely depleted grasping.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.61:1.13"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, sabbupādānapariyādānāya dhammo”ti. "
msgstr "This is the principle for depleting all fuel.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.61:1.14"
msgid "Navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

